The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | PNB sells 49% stake in arm
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      PNB sells 49% stake in arm
          OUR CORRESPONDENT                              
	New Delhi, Dec. 9: Punjab National Bank will sell 49 per cent of its housing finance arm to financial services firm Destimoney for Rs 217 crore in two phases.        
	In the first tranche, completed today, PNB sold 26 per cent in PNB Housing Finance for Rs 80 crore. The second stake sale will be completed after two years with Destimoney paying Rs 137 crore for the remaining 23 per cent.        
	Mumbai-based Destimoney Enterprises, formerly known as Dawnay Day, is a specialised retail financial services firm headed by Vivek Vig.         
	PNB has also restructured the board of the housing finance unit. G.N. Bajpai, former chairman of Sebi and the Life Insurance Corporation of India, and P.K. Gupta, ex-chairman of the National Housing Bank and the United Bank of India, have been appointed independent board members.                                                                                                                                       
